  trace.recordSubcall(node);
}
```

`trace.recordSubcall` mutates the `TraceBuilder`'s `subcalls` array and `accessed` Map. Recording is done sequentially after `runConcurrent` resolves, so there is no concurrent mutation of `trace` from parallel subcalls. This is **the key safety invariant** — parallel execution of `runSubcall` never touches `trace`. The `TraceBuilder` is only ever mutated from the single `execute` continuation after `await runConcurrent(…)` returns.

