`runConcurrent` stores results at `results[currentIndex]`, not by push, so the output array has the same order as the input `calls` array regardless of task completion order. This is verified by the test `"runs run_subcalls in parallel while preserving input order"` where task `b` and `c` complete before `a` yet the output is `[a, b, c]`. This ordering guarantee is correct.

