### Key Structural Observation

The system is safe today because of one critical invariant: **`TraceBuilder` is only ever mutated from a single async continuation at a time.** Parallel subcalls run inside `runConcurrent` and never touch `trace`; only the `execute` continuation that calls `await runConcurrent(…)` then records results in a sequential loop afterward. But this invariant is entirely implicit — it is not enforced by `TraceBuilder`'s API, not documented in its class definition, and not protected by any access control. A refactor that moves `trace.recordSubcall(node)` into the task lambda would silently introduce concurrent array mutations with no warning. The most impactful hardening step would be to make the recording step explicitly post-settlement — or, if live/streaming recording is ever needed, to introduce a proper queue or per-task accumulator that merges into the shared builder only at a safe synchronization point.

